{
  "stem": "15686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It certainly looks like we're just going there, and the Japanese are going to kill us because they are the Allies of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had already established what was then called the Axis, Berlin and Tokyo, although the war hadn't started yet.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Now it happened that one of my father's brothers-- my Uncle Richard-- was living in Paris.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had left Germany in 1933, because he was the head of the Berlin Grain Exchange, and he was on Nazi's hit list.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As soon as they took power, he was one of the people that was to be arrested.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But he was tipped off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So by night, he simply went by train to Paris.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In those days it was-- border controls were very loose--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--loose, because the Nazis had just taken over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he lived in Paris with his wife and little daughter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And somebody told my parents that there was a way to smuggle children into France and that the French authorities were very lax about verifying papers and things when it came to children, that they really didn't bother with children and that children could cross into France unmolested.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother said, well, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] let's do the following-- I think we're going to our certain deaths, and we'll make a copy of this quota paper that we have.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if God wants it, we'll all meet in the United States in a couple of years.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But you two are going to go and live with your Uncle Richard in Paris.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, it was terribly difficult for her, but she thought that better than to die in some far off place that they never heard of, we would be safer in Paris.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
